The Herald Tafadzwa Zimoyo
Senior Arts Reporter Gamuchirai Munyoro (20) retained the Miss Pan-African 2020-2021 for Zimbabwe at an event held in Accra, Ghana, last weekend. She succeeds compatriot Pauline Marere won the crown in the previous edition in Bayelsa, Nigeria. The first runner up to Munyoro was from Kenya, while the second runner up was from Sierra Leone. Munyoro won a car, US$3 000 and she will get international opportunities in the modelling and movie fields.